    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Kosher salt</Name>
      <Quantity units="TSP">1</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>To taste</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
  </Ingredients>
  <Method>
    <Step image="">In a large sauté pan, sauté bacon until brown and crisp, transfer to a mise bowl and hold. </Step>
    <Step image="">Add the potatoes, and onions and sauté until they begin to caramelize, add shallots and sauté for another couple of minutes.  Sprinkle flour over the pan, tossing contents to coat evenly. </Step>
    <Step image="">Add bottled clam juice and juice from clams.  Stir and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer, stirring occasionally until potatoes are fork tender.  Add previously cooked bacon. </Step>
    <Step image="">Mix in half-and-half and season with salt and pepper.  Add minced clams, heat until simmering.  Add heavy cream.  </Step>
    <Step image="">Garnish with parsley and bacon, serve with very warm sourdough bread and very cold dark beer. </Step>
  </Method>
